.SH NAME
device_set_wakeup_capable \- Set/reset device wakeup capability flag.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" device_set_wakeup_capable
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "bool capable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to handle.
.IP "capable" 12
Whether or not \fIdev\fP is capable of waking up the system from sleep.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIcapable\fP is set, set the \fIdev\fP's power.can_wakeup flag and add its
wakeup-related attributes to sysfs.  Otherwise, unset the \fIdev\fP's
power.can_wakeup flag and remove its wakeup-related attributes from sysfs.

This function may sleep and it can't be called from any context where
sleeping is not allowed.
